<ns4420:section xmlns:ns4420="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" xml:id="resources.information.technologies.java.j2se.swing.developingSwingInterfaces.textComponents.passwordFields">
    <ns4421:title xmlns:ns4421="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">Password Fields and
        Standard Dialog Boxes via JOptionPane</ns4421:title>
    <ns4422:para xmlns:ns4422="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">A password field is a text field which gives the user some indication of the number of
        characters typed in without showing the actual characters. In the following demonstration
        program we have a userName and password field and we allow users into our dungeons when the
        supplied password is "007".</ns4422:para>
    <ns4423:para xmlns:ns4423="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"/>
    <ns4424:para xmlns:ns4424="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
        <ns4425:programlisting xmlns:ns4425="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">
<xi:include xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" href="./src/TestPasswordField.java" parse="text"/>  
        </ns4425:programlisting>
    </ns4424:para>
    <ns4426:para xmlns:ns4426="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook"> When the correct password has been supplied a message box informing the user of this fact
        is displayed. Otherwise a message box with an error message is displayed. The resultant user
        interface is illustrated below. A range of standard dialog boxes is supplied by
        <ns4427:literal xmlns:ns4427="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">javax.swing.JOptionPane</ns4427:literal>. These include informational, warning and error
        message dialogs as well as standard "YES/NO" and "YES/NO/CANCEL" dialogs. Single-string
        input dialogs are also supplied by <ns4428:literal xmlns:ns4428="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook">JOptionPane</ns4428:literal>. </ns4426:para>
